The issue seems to be originating from ExprWalkerProcFactory::extractFinalCandidates():

{noformat}
    ExprInfo exprInfo = ctx.getExprInfo(expr);
    if (exprInfo != null && exprInfo.isCandidate) {
      ctx.addFinalCandidate(exprInfo.alias, exprInfo.convertedExpr != null ?
              exprInfo.convertedExpr : expr);
      return;
    }
{noformat}

When exprInfo.convertedExpr is used instead of expr, the original alias of expr is kept. In the tested case this is null and this leads, after a convoluted path, to the NPE (the expression is moved into non-candidates list as a {null=[null]} map and this ultimately gets read as a descriptor).
